# .gitignore for Terraform

# 1. Local execution and cache files
# ----------------------------------
.terraform/
# This directory contains the providers and modules. It's regenerated on 'terraform init'.

# 2. State files (CRITICAL)
# ----------------------------------
# Since you use Terraform Cloud, your state is stored remotely, 
# but local runs can sometimes generate these files. 
# NEVER commit these; they contain your raw infrastructure secrets.
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.*

# 3. Variable files (Where secrets live)
# ----------------------------------
# We exclude all .tfvars files because they often contain sensitive data.
*.tfvars
*.tfvars.json

# If you have specific, non-sensitive variables you WANT to commit, 
# you can use an override file (uncomment if needed):
# !variables.tfvars

# 4. Local environment variables/secrets
# ----------------------------------
.env
.envrc
# These are common for tools like direnv or local shell scripts.

# 5. Terraform Crash Logs
# ----------------------------------
crash.log
crash.*.log

# 6. Terraform Lock File
# ----------------------------------
# NOTE: It is generally recommended to COMMIT .terraform.lock.hcl 
# so your team (or your CI/CD) uses the exact same provider versions.
# If you want to ignore it (not recommended), uncomment the line below:
# .terraform.lock.hcl

# 7. OS/Editor specific
# ----------------------------------
.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp